He's had some success against San Francisco in the past, so starting him is advisable. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1203\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eMuhsin Muhammad\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR CAR - Orange Roughy \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMuhammad finally had a somewhat productive game, catching six passes for 75 yards against St. Louis. He's had some success in the past against this week's opponent, San Francisco, so starting him is a decent move. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http://football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1028\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eBrett Favre\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB GB - Dont Mess \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "otball215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1069\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eSteve McNair\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, QB TEN - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eMcNair's status is still in question for Sunday's game against Cincinnati due to an injured right thumb. He threw the ball during individual drills Friday, and according to published reports, is likely to play despite not being 100 percent. We don't recommend McNair this week as a result.\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1094\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eEmmitt Smith\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, RB DAL - Team Dick \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003e",
  "pdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eFaulk had a huge game against Carolina, proving that he is still the best Fantasy player in the league. He's a must-start every week, and should post solid numbers in Week 10 against New England. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=2330\u0026key=1366\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eErnie Conwell\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, TE STL - C-Dawg's Boyz \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eConwell has had a few down weeks, so starting him on your Fantasy team is somewhat of a gamble.   "Culpepper is one pace for a good Fantasy season despite the lack of consistency in Minnesota's offense this season. He's one of the better quarterbacks in the league from a Fantasy perspective, and should be in your starting lineup on a weekly basis. \u003c/FONT\u003e\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cA HREF=\"http": "//football215.fantasy.sportsline.com/mp/elink?script=players\u0026league=getbad\u0026owner=12050.9\u0026random=921\u0026key=1248\u0026\"\u003e\u003cB\u003eCris Carter\u003c/B\u003e\u003c/A\u003e, WR MIN - Luccis Losers \u003cFONT SIZE=1\u003eUpdated 11/16/01\u003c/FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eCarter's numbers may be down somewhat this season, but he's still too good to ever consider benching.   "Date": "Sun, 18 Nov 2001 07:38:52 -0800 (PST)",
  "FONT\u003e\u003cBR\u003e\u003cFONT FACE=\"Arial, Helvetica\"\u003e\u003cFONT SIZE=2\u003eAccording to published reports, Wycheck is expected to play half of Sunday's game against Cincinnati.   "From": "noreply@ccomad3.uu.commissioner.com",
  "Holt continues to put up consistent yardage totals, but he's only scored only three touchdowns this season.   "Taylor (groin) practiced without incident on Friday, but he still needs medical clearance before he can play in Sunday's game against Pittsburgh.   "October 24, 2001 - NOAA \u003chttp": "//www.noaa.gov/\u003e today unveiled two new indices that evaluate the effect of climate conditions on corn and soybean yield and on residential energy needs. The development of the indices is part of NOAA's \"Environomics\" program \u003chttp://lwf.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/climate/research/environomics/environomics.html\u003e, an effort to better understand the impact of weather and climate on socioeconomic sectors of the nation. The indices were developed by NOAA's National Climatic Data Center \u003chttp://lwf.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/ncdc.html\u003e in Asheville, N.C., which maintains the world's largest weather database. (Click NOAA image for larger view of standardized temperature index for Sept. 2001.)",

{

  "Content-Type": "text/plain; charset=us-ascii",
  "Date": "Fri, 9 Nov 2001 15:52:04 -0800 (PST)",
  "From": "chairman.ken@enron.com",
  "I know you have a lot of questions about this transaction and about next steps.  We have a list of frequently asked questions posted at \u003chttp": "//home.enron.com/updates/\u003e.
